{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:19:14.724689", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Objective\n- Objective: Assess current network health, detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, and identify root causes.\n- Environment: FRR OSPF multi-area enterprise with core/distribution/access hierarchy. Server farm 10.200.0.0/24 hosting DNS (10.200.0.2) and web servers web0–web3.\n\nSummary Assessment\n- Core and routing plane appear healthy. OSPF routes are present on distribution switches for all relevant subnets, including the server farm.\n- Server farm connectivity is normal (web servers reach DNS with low RTT).\n- Access subnet 10.2.1.0/24 is healthy (host_2_1_1_1 can reach DNS and web services; curl shows normal DNS lookup/TTFB).\n- A single end host anomaly is present: host_1_1_1_1 is misaddressed and cannot reach its gateway or any routed destinations.\n\nKey Findings and Evidence\n\n1) Reachability and Application Tests\n- host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.2/24, GW 10.2.1.1)\n  - ICMP to DNS: Success (rtt ≈ 2.8–5 ms).\n  - ICMP to web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): Success (rtt ≈ 2.7–5.1 ms).\n  - curl http://web0.local: Success with fast DNS lookup and total times ≈ 7–98 ms across trials.\n- host_1_1_1_1 (10.2.1.166/24, GW 10.2.1.1)\n  - ICMP to DNS (10.200.0.2): Destination Host Unreachable (from 10.2.1.166).\n  - ICMP to web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): Destination Host Unreachable (from 10.2.1.166).\n  - curl http://web0.local: name lookup time reported as 0 with total ≈ 3.9–5.0 s, indicative of failure/timeout to resolve or connect due to lack of reachability.\n  - ICMP to host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.2) on same /24: Destination Host Unreachable (from 10.2.1.166) — points to L2/Default GW reachability problem in local segment context.\n\n2) Host Configurations\n- host_1_1_1_1 network config:\n  - IP 10.2.1.166/24, default via 10.2.1.1\n  - /etc/resolv.conf: nameserver 10.200.0.2\n- host_2_1_1_1 network config:\n  - IP 10.2.1.2/24, default via 10.2.1.1\n  - /etc/resolv.conf: nameserver 10.200.0.2\n\n3) Distribution Layer Routing and Reachability\n- switch_dist_1_1 (intended GW for 10.1.1.0/24)\n  - br0: 10.1.1.1/24, OSPF learned routes to 10.2.1.0/24 and 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\n  - ICMP to dns_server: Success (rtt ≈ 1.2–2.6 ms).\n  - ICMP to host_1_1_1_1 (10.2.1.166): Destination Host Unreachable reported by 172.16.0.11 (downstream dist_2_1), indicating the network correctly forwards toward 10.2.1.0/24 but the target is not present on that L2 segment.\n- switch_dist_2_1 (GW for 10.2.1.0/24)\n  - br0: 10.2.1.1/24, OSPF routes present for other subnets, including 10.200.0.0/24.\n  - ICMP to dns_server: Success (rtt ≈ 2.0–2.4 ms).\n  - ICMP to host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.2): Success.\n- OSPF tables on both distribution devices show expected routes for all infrastructure and user subnets and the server farm.\n\n4) Server Farm Health\n- web_server_0/1/2/3 -> dns_server ICMP: Success with low RTTs (≈1.5–2.2 ms). Indicates server access domain and DNS server are reachable within OSPF domain.\n\nAnomaly Detected\n- host_1_1_1_1 is misconfigured for the wrong subnet. Based on topology, host_1_1_1_1 belongs under switch_dist_1_1 (10.1.1.0/24, GW 10.1.1.1). However, it has IP 10.2.1.166/24 and default GW 10.2.1.1 (switch_dist_2_1). This causes:\n  - Failure to ARP the configured gateway (no 10.2.1.1 on its L2 segment).\n  - Destination Host Unreachable for any off-subnet traffic, including DNS and server farm.\n  - Network-wide attempts to reach 10.2.1.166 are routed to the 10.2.1.0/24 segment via dist_2_1, where the host is not present (as evidenced by ICMP unreachable from 172.16.0.11).\n\nFault Localization\n- Faulty device: host_1_1_1_1.\n- Adjacent infrastructure (switch_access_1_1_1 and switch_dist_1_1) appears correctly configured: dist_1_1 has 10.1.1.1/24 on br0 and valid OSPF routes; server reachability from other domains is normal.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Static IP/gateway misconfiguration on host_1_1_1_1: assigned 10.2.1.166/24 with default GW 10.2.1.1 while physically connected to the 10.1.1.0/24 broadcast domain whose gateway is 10.1.1.1.\n\nImpact\n- host_1_1_1_1 cannot reach DNS or web services; cannot communicate with hosts even in what it believes is its own subnet (10.2.1.0/24) due to being on a different L2 domain.\n- No evidence of broader routing or service impact; OSPF and server farm services are functioning for correctly addressed hosts.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 15338, "output_tokens": 3952, "total_tokens": 19290, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 14976}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2496}}}
